summary: In a groundbreaking move, the UK House of Commons has approved a bill to prohibit anyone born after 2009 from purchasing cigarettes in an effort to create a "smoke-free" generation. This legislation, known as the UK smoking ban, aims to reduce smoking prevalence and its associated health risks. The bill, proposed by Chancellor Rishi Sunak, has sparked controversy among Conservative MPs and garnered international attention as the world's first generational smoking ban. The bill's implementation timeline and enforcement measures are still under debate, but its passage marks a significant step towards the UK's goal of eliminating smoking-related illnesses.

summary: Blake Griffin, a former All-Star and Rookie of the Year winner, has announced his retirement from the NBA after 13 seasons. Griffin's career was hampered by injuries and a trade that took him away from his long-time team, the Los Angeles Clippers. Despite his challenges, Griffin had a successful 14-year career, earning six All-Star selections and playing for four different teams. His retirement comes after a season with the Brooklyn Nets, where he averaged 6.4 points and 4.1 rebounds per game. Griffin's career earnings are estimated to be around $172 million, and he is considered a potential candidate for the Basketball Hall of Fame.

The campaign, titled "The Original Mouthful," aims to "pass the baton of the chant between generations." This modern take on the classic promotion extends the "The Original Mouthful" campaign, which launched in September 2022. The challenge is being promoted through a variety of channels, including social media, television, and in-store signage.
